        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="45" name="Message" rows="6" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
Let me start by saying, to all you Necro’s who have your way of doing things, do it your way. This is not meant to be the only way they can be done, but rather the way I did them. So modify it to suit your style of play.

First thing, you need to get the key to Cobalt Scar. There are a couple of ways to get it. The way I chose was to kill the Drake that drops it in Skyshrine. There is plenty of info out there on obtaining this key. Once you have the key you can then enter Cobalt. 

Spells I used… Dark, Fear, BOD, Lich, Splurt, LT lvl 1 and the lvl 49 LT, Gate.

Once you zone in, you will be standing on a platform. The ramp leading up into the tower leads to the exit. The exit is surrounded by 5 Wyverns that do not see invis. If you will look to your left after zoning in, you will see a wyvern standing at the end of the ledge all by his self. This will be your first target. Go down and under the platform and make a pet under the ramp leading to the tower. Park him here and pull the single wyvern that you saw when you zoned in with your lvl one lifetap. Once he gets to your pet send him in. Hit him with Dark then fear and back your pet off. Pop him with BOD and splurt. Cast lich and sit down. The Wyvern will then walk out over the top of the mountain down the middle towards the big rock. Just before he gets to the rock fear wears off. Once he starts getting within Draks casting range stand up and hit him with Dark again. Allow him to come back to you and time it so that you fear him pretty close to the platform. He is now getting close to being dead. Once splurt wears off, send in the pet and let him finish it. Make sure you stay close to him during this time or he will gate back to his spawn point.

Once the single spawn is dead, you will notice there are 2 sets of spawns on each side of the mountain. One has 2 spawns and the other has 3. You can single pull the wyverns because they have a very small agro range. Repeat the method as stated above for each spawn. With Lich and BOD you should maintain about 80 mana through all of them. About the time you get done with the 5 spawns, the first one should be popping and you can start the cycle over. It is non stop killing and the XP is decent. I soloed here from 52 to 53 in one 12 hour day. This was before the XP changes so not sure how good the XP is now. One more tid bit of info, do not allow the wyverns to go past the big rock out in the middle of the mountain. There is a drake that flies close to it and if it agroes then be prepared to run or gate. If you follow the plan I laid out above this should never happen.

Down off the mountain there are Otter people called Othmir. There are some merchants there you can sell to. They will also act as guards for you if you get into trouble. But be WARNED, they do not like skeletons so be sure and remove Lich and don’t drag you pet down there cause they will attack it and you next.

I am not sure at what level you could start hunting here. I started them at 52. Nor do I know how high you can go with them. My guess is they will start greening at about 54. I was able to get tons of rare jewels from them as well.

I hope this helps and turns you onto a new solo spot post 50. Like I said at the beginning, there are always numerous ways to hunt as a necro. So use what you like the best. Just use what I laid out here as a guide as to what you can expect.



Fallonn Vargyle
Erudite Necromancer of the
Sacred Order of Shadows
Level 53
Karana Server

[/quote]</textarea><br>
        

