      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Aanr</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Any Necro worth a grain of salt should be here after he/she is done getting to 49 from the Bloodgill's.  This place might rival the Bloodgill's as the best experience in the game.  Unfortunately I didn't get here till 51, but they are ridiculously easy at 51 on.  My guess at 49-51 would be to fear kite on the beach using the standard fear kiting techniques.  At 51 is where the fun begins.  I can kill these with only 4 spells root-dotting.  I find a nice blue (even the green ones still give good exp) and pull it with splurt.  Once it get's off the hill and on the beach, I root it.  Apply darkness (I use dooming, only need it for the snare), then I cast e-bolt if my health isn't below 60%.  If my health is below 60%, I cast BoD first.  Once all 4 spells are on it, I sit and med.  I keep lich on all the time.  As soon as the mob dies, I'm between 80-100% mana and about 80% health.  These are nonstop killing.  I am currently averaging about 1 and a half blue bubble an hour.  About 1 out of 8 kills you will get a gem.  Some of these gems are used for the Velious armor quests, some are just merchant fodder, but GREAT merchant fodder.  The trash gems sell for about 50pp to the merchants.  I've made well over 1.5kpp here in 1 and a half levels and I have 12 Nephrite (used for INT caster pants quest) and 6 flawed topaz (used for INT arms quest).  I've also gotten the melee arms and legs gems.  You can sometimes sell those for 1kpp a piece.  I see alot of posts on the general board on where to hunt at 51, if you aren't here you don't know what levelling is.  I plan on getting to 54 here then seeing if I can do the wizard's in Neriak without taking a faction hit against the dead.</P><P>Aanr<BR>52 Dark Elf Necromancer<BR>Seventh Hammer Server</font></td>
